<br>
Moves between the isles were fairy speedy once we got the coffin process down. I don't believe we had sufficient turn out on Saturday to clear back to isle 5 again, I was working at that day and don't know how many we had show, so people that wished to join the raid that day were coffined up to join the fun.<br>
<br>
The raid was planned for 55+ on Sunday only. We had the coffin proccess down so well at that point there was little point in not bringing everyone else as long as we had the coffins. I think most of those that attended had a good time. <br>
<br>
They say hind sight is 20/20 so there are things I'd do differently next time as far as planning:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Designate a core group of 24 that get keys off every isle.<br>
<br>
Everyone beyond that core group would be required to bring small coffins, 61p each, for each isle they wish to go to.<br>
<br>
No limit on those attending unless it would adversely affect the time required between islands</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Live, Raid and Learn.<br>
